  <section class='page-section headline background right first'>
  <img class='bg-image' src="/images/ec/ho_banner_roofline_4-2.jpg" alt="" />
  <div class='container'>
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-md-12 headline">
        <h1>Soffit & Fascia</h1>
        <h2>Hassle-free, low maintenance roofline solutions.</h2>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>


<section class='page-section centered'>
  <div class='container'>
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-md-12">
        <h2>Protect your home from the elements.</h2>
        <p class='big'>
          With any home improvement project, it’s important to get the foundations right. Making sure the exterior of your home is fully protected against the elements is just as important as looking after the interior. Fascias, soffits and gutters may not grab the headlines design-wise, but they play a crucial role in protecting your home from damage.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>



<section class='page-section left'>
  <div class='container'>
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-md-6">
        <img src="/images/upvc-guttering-fascia-soffits-black.jpg" alt="" />
      </div>
      <div class="col-md-6 benefits">
        <h2>Fascia Boards</h2>
        <p>
          All our UPVC fascia boards are manufactured by us. That means that all the colours offered across our entire roofing accessories range match perfectly.  And we have 8 different colours and finishes to choose from. All our whites are the same, all our woodgrain finishes match perfectly. Our fascia boards are made from 18mm thick high quality UPVC. That means they are strong and weather-proof, the ideal long-term protection for your roof.
        </p>

        <p>
          <h3><i class="fa fa-check"></i> Requires little maintenance</h3>
        </p>
        <p>
          <h3><i class="fa fa-check"></i> No sanding, painting or treatment necessary</h3>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>



<section class='page-section right'>
  <div class='container'>
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-md-6 col-md-push-6">
        <img src="/images/2_194_e.jpg" alt="" />
      </div>
      <div class="col-md-6 col-md-pull-6 benefits">
        <h2>Soffit Boards</h2>
        <p>
          There are lots of options to help you create the right look for your home. Our UPVC soffit boards come in eight different widths, eight different colours and two styles: standard plain and a decorative ‘ogee’.
        </p>

        <p>
          <h3><i class="fa fa-check"></i> Ventilation slots to ensure constant airflow</h3>
        </p>
        <p>
          <h3><i class="fa fa-check"></i> Long-term weather proofing for your roof</h3>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>



<section class='page-section left'>
  <div class='container'>
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-md-6">
        <img src="/images/2_141.png" alt="" />
      </div>
      <div class="col-md-6 benefits">
        <h2>Capping Boards</h2>
        <p>
          As long as your existing timber fascia is rot-free, a UPVC capping board can be fitted. It’s a cost effective alternative to freshen up your home’s exterior and although your capping board has a very important function – to protect your roof and support your gutters – that doesn’t mean it has to look functional.
        </p>
        <p>
          <h3><i class="fa fa-check"></i> Fit easily over existing fascia boards</h3>
        </p>
        <p>
          <h3><i class="fa fa-check"></i> 9mm thick UPVC board for long-lasting protection</h3>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class='page-section right'>
  <div class='container'>
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-md-6 col-md-push-6">
        <img src="/images/Guttering-1.jpg" alt="" />
      </div>
      <div class="col-md-6 col-md-pull-6 benefits">
        <h2>Guttering</h2>
        <p>
          Damage from damp can cause a lot of problems, both inside and outside your home. Worst of all, once moisture has found its way in, it can be expensive to remedy. Having a reliable, robust drainage system will protect your property from water ingress.
        </p>
        <p>
          <h3><i class="fa fa-check"></i> Hard-wearing components that are made to last</h3>
        </p>
        <p>
          <h3><i class="fa fa-check"></i> Interchangeable, bespoke drainage systems</h3>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>



<section class='page-section right texture'>
  <div class='container'>
